This paper deals with natural language generation and style transfer, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses neural networks for training and modeling, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of controls to manipulate the style of generated text, which is related to the field of control theory (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions image processing and style transfer, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
